summary: Following a Bachelor’s degree in Science with a specialization in Biological techniques, I have completed Master’s degree in Biotechnology with a specialization in isolation of industrially important amylase from Aspergillus  niger and its characterization .During my studies I have learnt a lot about independent research, lab work and scientific research .About my previous job, I have been a trained biotechnology faculty  for 11 years. I have spent past few years of my career preparing the students for their diploma programme examination and internal assessment, which has given me hands-on experience in handling laboratory equipment, conducting experiments and laboratory management. I am a hardworking and energetic individual with excellent communication and supervisory skills. Organized and dependable candidate successful at managing multiple priorities with a positive attitude. Willingness to take on added responsibilities to meet team goals.My current job at  avantor sciences even more emphasize in continuing  my career in a GMP laboratory. I am  fully trained  for GMP and GLP.
